# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# mr7.ai — Security Layer Environment Variables
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Copy what you need into .env or Replit Secrets.

# ── Layer 1: AES-256-GCM Encryption Key ─────────────
# Used to encrypt personal API keys stored in the DB.
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
AES_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-64-char-hex-string-here

# ── Layer 2: RSA Key Pair for JWT Signing ────────────
# Generate:
#   openssl genrsa -out jwt_private.pem 2048
#   openssl rsa -in jwt_private.pem -pubout -out jwt_public.pem
#   Then paste each file content as a single line with \n for newlines.
JWT_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"
JWT_PUBLIC_KEY="-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n...\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----"

# JWT access token expiry (default: 1h)
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=1h

# ── Layer 3: Session Secret ──────────────────────────
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
SESSION_SECRET=your-session-secret-here

# ── Layer 4: CORS — Allowed Origins ─────────────────
# Comma-separated list. If unset, all origins are allowed (dev only).
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://mr7.ai,https://www.mr7.ai

# ── Layer 5: CSP / App Domain ───────────────────────
APP_DOMAIN=mr7.ai
# Additional CDN origins for CSP (comma-separated)
CSP_CDN_ORIGINS=

# ── Layer 6: Security Alerts ─────────────────────────
# Slack/Discord/SIEM webhook for real-time attack alerts (optional)
SECURITY_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/...

# Separate webhook for weekly security reports (optional, falls back to SECURITY_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL)
SECURITY_REPORT_WEBHOOK_URL=

# ── Layer 7: Database ────────────────────────────────
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/mr7ai

# ── Layer 8: Internal API Key ────────────────────────
# Shared secret between frontend and API server
INTERNAL_API_KEY=your-internal-key-here

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# QUICK GENERATION COMMANDS (run these in terminal):
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# AES_ENCRYPTION_KEY:  openssl rand -hex 32
# SESSION_SECRET:      openssl rand -hex 32
# INTERNAL_API_KEY:    openssl rand -hex 24
# RSA pair:
#   openssl genrsa -out /tmp/jwt.pem 2048
#   openssl rsa -in /tmp/jwt.pem -pubout -out /tmp/jwt.pub.pem
#   cat /tmp/jwt.pem   # → JWT_PRIVATE_KEY
#   cat /tmp/jwt.pub.pem  # → JWT_PUBLIC_KEY
